It's kind of tricky really, if you think you can mirror the writing style of someone and not be spotted, and they have been 'cleared' as a good role, you can try shifting into them.
people like to try and shift into the Seer for example, then you can start misleading the town.
but a safer option is to shift into someone the seer has checked as good, then fly under the radar.
some people are good at spotting shifts, but most are kind of bad at it unless they really go looking.

another thing to consider is how active the person you shift into is, if they are on their phone all day, talking at random times, and you can't match that, you'll need a convincing excuse. Such as "I was on vacation, but back at work now" or something.
